theorem Topology.closed_denseInterior_eq_univ {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hDenseInt : Dense (interior (A : Set X))) :
    (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  -- Density of `interior A` gives `closure (interior A) = univ`.
  have h_closure_int : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    hDenseInt.closure_eq
  -- Since `interior A ⊆ A`, taking closures yields `closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A = A`.
  have h_subset : closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ (A : Set X) := by
    have h_int_sub : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ (A : Set X) := interior_subset
    have h_closure_mono :
        closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
      closure_mono h_int_sub
    simpa [hA_closed.closure_eq] using h_closure_mono
  -- The two inclusions together give the desired equality.
  have : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ (A : Set X) := by
    simpa [h_closure_int] using h_subset
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm this Set.Subset_univ

theorem Topology.P1_inter_of_open {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) (hB : IsOpen (B : Set X)) :
    Topology.P1 (X := X) (A ∩ B) := by
  have h_open : IsOpen ((A ∩ B) : Set X) := hA.inter hB
  exact isOpen_subset_closureInterior (X := X) (A := A ∩ B) h_open
